HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 295
BY REPRESENTATIVES JACOB LANDRY, CHASSION, AND SPELL
A RESOLUTION
To establish and recognize the Energy Caucus of the House of Representatives and to
provide relative to the caucus.
WHEREAS, the energy industry is vital to Louisiana's economy; and
WHEREAS, the energy sector is multifaceted, involving fossil fuels, renewable
energy, and nuclear power; and
WHEREAS, several members of the House of Representatives work or have worked
in the energy sector; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana House of Representatives recognizes the importance of
fostering a specialized and subject-specific caucus dedicated to matters involving the energy
industry.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby establish and recognize the Energy Caucus of the
House of Representatives.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that every member of the House of Representatives
who works in, has worked in, or has an interest in promoting the energy sector may be a
member of the Energy Caucus.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
